        "text": {
          "content": "2\n*\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0001\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0001\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0001\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0001\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0002\u0000\u0000\u0002\u007fDrone Component\n\nThe Drone component is a 3D Object that connects to a compatible joystick component (for example the xboxForWindows component found in the TDVR/System Components folder in the Palette.\n\nInputs:\n\nExpects a compatible joystick component with a\nchild 'chansOut' CHOP.\n\nChannels must be mapped correctly using the \n'Channel Name Mappings' page above.\n\nOutputs:\n\nThe output of this component is the 'constraint' geo object. Connect this tranform to another \nobject using its local 'Constrain To' parameter. Notice this special internal component is \"Published\" on the top level custom components page in the Published OPs page.",
          "is_binary": false
